race.comment: TAKE ACHANCE ON ME (3) showed plenty of determination when breaking her maiden at the Sunshine Coast. That win should give her confidence and she looks well placed to go on with it now. MUSIC FEVER (5) was close-up when resuming here over 1100m, beaten less than a length after racing on speed. Fitter for that effort and kept fresh since, she looms as a major danger. BLITZWATER (4) returned with a solid third and now has the blinkers applied, which should sharpen him considerably. Still lightly raced and open to further improvement. JUNGLE LAW (1) worked home soundly into sixth last start and looks better suited stepping up in trip. The claim helps under the big weight and he has winning figures at his best.
